1
00:00:15,060 --> 00:00:17,510
♪The world keeps changing♪

2
00:00:17,510 --> 00:00:19,980
♪A thousand years pass
in the blink of an eye♪

3
00:00:19,980 --> 00:00:22,160
♪Shoulder to shoulder♪

4
00:00:22,160 --> 00:00:24,400
♪We stand above the world♪

5
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:26,590
♪Our identities switch♪

6
00:00:26,750 --> 00:00:29,320
♪The world turns upside down♪

7
00:00:29,730 --> 00:00:31,730
♪Watch me♪

8
00:00:31,730 --> 00:00:35,320
♪Stir up a storm♪

9
00:00:35,320 --> 00:00:37,610
♪Let's time-travel, bro♪

10
00:00:37,610 --> 00:00:40,060
♪Our blood is boiling♪

11
00:00:40,060 --> 00:00:45,290
♪The genius emperor
plots with brilliant strategy♪

12
00:00:45,290 --> 00:00:49,710
♪The slacker general
is unmatched in battle♪

13
00:00:49,710 --> 00:00:52,200
♪The business
world is in turmoil♪

14
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:54,750
♪The court is
rife with intrigue♪

15
00:00:54,750 --> 00:00:59,170
♪We will conquer the world♪

16
00:00:59,170 --> 00:01:03,510
♪There's no escape
for the traitors♪

17
00:01:05,080 --> 00:01:08,000
=No Way! My Bro Is the Emperor=

18
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:11,160
=Episode 3=

19
00:01:23,110 --> 00:01:24,630
Officials,

20
00:01:24,790 --> 00:01:26,310
what's decided here

21
00:01:26,950 --> 00:01:29,270
concerns your entire families.

22
00:01:29,840 --> 00:01:31,010
You should

23
00:01:32,590 --> 00:01:34,410
think twice.

24
00:01:34,410 --> 00:01:35,110
Uh.

25
00:01:35,110 --> 00:01:36,400
What do we do?

26
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:38,680
Our families' lives are at stake.

27
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:39,840
Right.

28
00:01:40,950 --> 00:01:43,070
General Sun is right.

29
00:01:43,070 --> 00:01:43,760
I

30
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:44,800
second the motion.

31
00:01:45,440 --> 00:01:46,950
I second the motion.

32
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:48,200
- I second the motion!
- I second the motion!

33
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:48,840
You all...

34
00:01:48,840 --> 00:01:49,670
- I second the motion!
- I second the motion!

35
00:01:49,670 --> 00:01:51,240
This is outrageous.

36
00:01:54,440 --> 00:01:55,950
Obviously, this is the will

37
00:01:56,270 --> 00:01:59,390
of the officials and the army.

38
00:02:01,030 --> 00:02:03,070
If Your Majesty refuses...

39
00:02:03,070 --> 00:02:04,120
Sun Beiming.

40
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:08,200
You think

41
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:10,990
kidnapping their families

42
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:13,880
will force me to abdicate?

43
00:02:14,510 --> 00:02:16,240
This empire

44
00:02:16,630 --> 00:02:19,160
isn't yours

45
00:02:19,990 --> 00:02:21,800
for the taking.

46
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:26,320
(Bei Gu,)

47
00:02:26,430 --> 00:02:28,470
(I'm betting my life on you.)

48
00:02:28,870 --> 00:02:30,520
(If you don't back soon, it'll be over.)

49
00:02:31,480 --> 00:02:33,520
If unrest breaks out in the army,

50
00:02:33,870 --> 00:02:35,430
I'm afraid

51
00:02:35,430 --> 00:02:38,390
I won't be able
to keep Your Majesty alive.

52
00:02:49,510 --> 00:02:50,430
Is everything okay?

53
00:03:01,658 --> 00:03:04,110
Who says I can't fight?

54
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:06,880
Grandfather!

55
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:10,520
Official Liu,

56
00:03:10,620 --> 00:03:11,920
don't you think it's a coincidence?

57
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:13,880
I happened to be outside the palace

58
00:03:14,230 --> 00:03:15,920
and found this child who had gotten lost.

59
00:03:15,920 --> 00:03:17,430
Turns out

60
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:19,390
he's your grandson.

61
00:03:20,670 --> 00:03:21,590
Boy,

62
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:23,320
is everyone in the family

63
00:03:23,480 --> 00:03:24,920
fine?

64
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:28,390
Some bad guys wouldn't let us go home.

65
00:03:28,510 --> 00:03:30,640
Thanks to this mister.

66
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:33,800
He chases them away.

67
00:03:34,230 --> 00:03:35,640
Official Guo,

68
00:03:35,790 --> 00:03:36,710
Official Gao,

69
00:03:36,760 --> 00:03:37,830
Official Zhou.

70
00:03:38,510 --> 00:03:39,990
Your families

71
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,830
asked me to pass along a message.

72
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:43,040
Head home early

73
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:44,270
when the court is dismissed.

74
00:03:45,790 --> 00:03:47,240
Who do you think you are?

75
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:49,230
Who let you into the hall?

76
00:03:49,230 --> 00:03:50,150
Guards!

77
00:03:50,720 --> 00:03:52,200
Throw him out!

78
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:53,520
I'd like to see you try.

79
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:57,640
Gu Bei, step forward.

80
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,520
I hereby appoint you

81
00:04:00,630 --> 00:04:03,080
Fourth-Rank Cavalry General.

82
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,480
You have the right to attend court.

83
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:06,200
Your Majesty,

84
00:04:06,630 --> 00:04:08,320
General Sun's remarks

85
00:04:08,320 --> 00:04:09,480
were an insult to the throne.

86
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:11,080
He deserves to die.

87
00:04:11,280 --> 00:04:12,800
What are you waiting for?

88
00:04:14,070 --> 00:04:15,920
Drag this traitor

89
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:18,110
out and execute him.

90
00:04:18,150 --> 00:04:19,240
Wait.

91
00:04:22,480 --> 00:04:23,990
General Sun

92
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:25,830
committed no crime.

93
00:04:26,270 --> 00:04:28,110
Instead, he rendered a great service.

94
00:04:31,570 --> 00:04:32,730
(No backup.)

95
00:04:32,730 --> 00:04:34,200
(Can't take him on.)

96
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:35,550
(Got it.)

97
00:04:35,550 --> 00:04:36,500
(Watch this.)

98
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:39,150
His Majesty is right.

99
00:04:39,390 --> 00:04:40,990
If you want progress,

100
00:04:41,350 --> 00:04:42,510
you need differing opinions.

101
00:04:42,510 --> 00:04:44,830
You need people who dare to disagree.

102
00:04:45,040 --> 00:04:47,520
General Sun's advice

103
00:04:47,520 --> 00:04:50,330
was meant to spur His Majesty on,

104
00:04:50,330 --> 00:04:51,670
to keep him vigilant

105
00:04:51,670 --> 00:04:52,720
and never complacent.

106
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:54,910
It was not defiance.

107
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:56,950
General Gu has a point.

108
00:04:57,070 --> 00:04:58,200
General Sun

109
00:04:58,200 --> 00:04:59,830
risked his life to speak up.

110
00:05:00,550 --> 00:05:01,550
He deserves a reward.

111
00:05:04,790 --> 00:05:05,870
General Sun,

112
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:07,640
kneel and accept His Majesty's reward.

113
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:10,270
Has His Majesty's army arrived?

114
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:12,110
They will be here soon.

115
00:05:19,950 --> 00:05:20,870
I

116
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:23,830
thank Your Majesty.

117
00:05:25,190 --> 00:05:26,400
These two characters

118
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:28,550
are my expectations of you.

119
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:31,400
I bestow them upon you.

120
00:05:33,790 --> 00:05:34,960
Ministers,

121
00:05:35,670 --> 00:05:36,870
the court is dismissed.

122
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:53,160
(You moron.)

123
00:05:55,750 --> 00:05:56,920
What is His Majesty

124
00:05:57,550 --> 00:05:58,960
trying to get at?

125
00:06:11,160 --> 00:06:12,840
(Honor Learning and Confucianism)

126
00:06:12,840 --> 00:06:14,510
That was the perfect chance.

127
00:06:14,870 --> 00:06:16,310
Why didn't you kill

128
00:06:16,310 --> 00:06:17,630
that scoundrel?

129
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:19,870
His men are outside the palace.

130
00:06:20,190 --> 00:06:21,190
If we fight head-on,

131
00:06:21,550 --> 00:06:22,600
we'll lose.

132
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:23,720
We have to lie low for now.

133
00:06:24,350 --> 00:06:25,110
We need a plan

134
00:06:25,110 --> 00:06:26,430
to get rid of that Sun fellow

135
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:32,480
(Gu Nan, Consort of Jing)

136
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:35,520
Brother!

137
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:40,040
Brother, you've been on the frontier
for three years.

138
00:06:40,280 --> 00:06:42,040
I finally get to see you again.

139
00:06:42,430 --> 00:06:43,620
Bro...

140
00:06:43,990 --> 00:06:44,600
ther?

141
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:45,040
(Right.)

142
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:47,020
(Gu Bei had a younger sister.)

143
00:06:47,110 --> 00:06:48,030
Nan,

144
00:06:49,190 --> 00:06:50,430
I've never amounted to much,

145
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:53,430
but I spent all my savings
to buy you this silver hairpin.

146
00:06:56,400 --> 00:06:57,750
(After I left for the frontier,)

147
00:06:57,870 --> 00:06:59,720
(she entered the palace as a consort.)

148
00:07:04,040 --> 00:07:05,240
(I'll look after her)

149
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:06,480
(for the original Gu Bei.)

150
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:17,630
You're hitting on women in the palace?

151
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:19,550
Gu Nan.

152
00:07:20,110 --> 00:07:21,030
Gu Bei.

153
00:07:21,080 --> 00:07:22,000
My sister.

154
00:07:25,430 --> 00:07:26,520
Princess Hulv,

155
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:27,990
you're a heroine.

156
00:07:28,300 --> 00:07:30,190
Thanks to you for protecting me.

157
00:07:30,230 --> 00:07:31,300
What reward do you want?

158
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:32,520
Emperor of Jing,

159
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:35,080
I followed Gu Bei here because I want
to take him back to the plains

160
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:36,110
to run Xiaoyao Pavilion.

161
00:07:43,520 --> 00:07:44,440
Well...

162
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:48,480
Gu Bei is my trusted aide.

163
00:07:49,670 --> 00:07:50,640
For now,

164
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:51,840
I can't let him leave.

165
00:07:52,350 --> 00:07:53,360
How about this?

166
00:07:53,670 --> 00:07:55,800
I'll fund

167
00:07:55,840 --> 00:07:57,480
a Xiaoyao Pavilion branch in the plains.

168
00:07:57,720 --> 00:07:58,540
How's that?

169
00:07:58,540 --> 00:08:00,210
You'll pay

170
00:08:00,870 --> 00:08:02,400
to open one for me?

171
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:06,920
That's a great deal.

172
00:08:07,870 --> 00:08:09,160
With Xiaoyao Pavilion,

173
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:12,360
we can foster trade
between Jing and the plains.

174
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:15,110
The two nations can live in peace.

175
00:08:15,550 --> 00:08:16,670
Wouldn't that be better?

176
00:08:16,920 --> 00:08:18,840
We make money through trade

177
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,990
and enjoy ourselves at Xiaoyao Pavilion.

178
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:22,670
Who would want to go to war?

179
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:24,640
Deal.

180
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:26,670
I'll write to my father right away.

181
00:08:30,230 --> 00:08:31,150
You.

182
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:33,190
Are you not coming back with me?

183
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:36,280
His Majesty wants me to stay.

184
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:38,070
I can't

185
00:08:38,750 --> 00:08:40,430
defy an imperial decree.

186
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:44,990
If you're not coming back,

187
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:48,600
I'll stay.

188
00:08:49,990 --> 00:08:51,670
First, I can learn

189
00:08:51,670 --> 00:08:53,190
how to run Xiaoyao Pavilion.

190
00:08:53,310 --> 00:08:55,160
Second, if you get into trouble again,

191
00:08:55,350 --> 00:08:56,800
you'll need someone watching your back.

192
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:11,640
Hulv.

193
00:09:16,870 --> 00:09:17,790
Thanks.

194
00:09:20,310 --> 00:09:21,230
Don't mention it.

195
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:28,000
Granted.

196
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:35,540
Your Majesty, tonight...

197
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:38,920
Didn't I tell you?

198
00:09:39,160 --> 00:09:40,360
No consorts.

199
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:42,440
Don't ask again.

200
00:09:42,690 --> 00:09:43,750
Yes, Your Majesty.

201
00:09:51,060 --> 00:09:53,450
You have so many beauties in the harem,
and you don't touch a single one.

202
00:09:53,450 --> 00:09:55,240
What a waste of being Emperor.

203
00:09:56,760 --> 00:09:57,680
Tell me,

204
00:09:58,360 --> 00:09:59,790
who can you really trust?

205
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:02,920
Sure.

206
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:04,590
Eunuch Xu.

207
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:06,390
A few shadow guards.

208
00:10:07,310 --> 00:10:08,400
And now you.

209
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:10,320
That's all?

210
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:14,390
Not even ten people.

211
00:10:14,880 --> 00:10:16,600
And you're against over three thousand.

212
00:10:17,160 --> 00:10:18,790
No wonder that old geezer is so cocky.

213
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:27,280
Gu Bei,

214
00:10:27,670 --> 00:10:28,550
you don't have to

215
00:10:28,550 --> 00:10:29,990
stay in this mess with me.

216
00:10:31,070 --> 00:10:32,270
I'll let you leave tomorrow.

217
00:10:32,920 --> 00:10:33,960
Go back to the frontier

218
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:35,110
and live an easy life.

219
00:10:40,070 --> 00:10:40,990
Let me ask you.

220
00:10:41,830 --> 00:10:42,870
What are we?

221
00:10:44,160 --> 00:10:45,080
Father and son.

222
00:10:45,730 --> 00:10:46,750
Grandfather and grandson.

223
00:10:50,470 --> 00:10:51,560
Brothers.

224
00:10:51,710 --> 00:10:53,320
That's right.

225
00:10:53,430 --> 00:10:54,590
After all those years

226
00:10:54,590 --> 00:10:56,600
you let me copy your final exams,

227
00:10:56,640 --> 00:10:58,510
there's no way I'm leaving you now.

228
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:01,320
I've got a plan.

229
00:11:02,190 --> 00:11:03,110
We...

230
00:11:12,640 --> 00:11:13,920
He sure has gone all out

231
00:11:13,920 --> 00:11:15,680
planting spies around me.

232
00:11:17,670 --> 00:11:18,680
Now tell me.

233
00:11:18,830 --> 00:11:20,320
Besides making grenades,

234
00:11:20,430 --> 00:11:21,350
what else have you built?

235
00:11:32,560 --> 00:11:34,420
♪Let's time-travel, bro♪

236
00:11:34,420 --> 00:11:36,800
♪Our spirit soars to the skies♪

237
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:42,240
♪The brainy emperor plots the strategy♪

238
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:46,620
♪The slacker general leads the charge♪

239
00:11:46,620 --> 00:11:49,030
♪Swords clash and warhorses thunder♪

240
00:11:49,030 --> 00:11:51,570
♪Let the history judge our deeds♪

241
00:11:51,570 --> 00:11:57,240
♪Our brotherhood is priceless♪

242
00:11:57,240 --> 00:12:02,800
♪Peace across the land, carefree at last♪

243
00:12:07,090 --> 00:12:09,150
♪Funny moments never stop♪

244
00:12:09,770 --> 00:12:11,960
♪Silly blunders never cease♪

245
00:12:12,180 --> 00:12:16,330
♪Yet through every up and down♪

246
00:12:16,330 --> 00:12:18,300
♪We create miracles♪

247
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:21,060
♪From naive youths♪

248
00:12:21,320 --> 00:12:23,800
♪To legendary heroes♪

249
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:25,750
♪This journey♪

250
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:29,760
♪Is one we'll be proud of♪

251
00:12:29,760 --> 00:12:32,310
♪Let's time-travel, bro♪

252
00:12:34,780 --> 00:12:37,650
♪Let's create♪

253
00:12:39,690 --> 00:12:47,610
♪A legend of our own♪

